Key Match Events: Jack Grealish got England on the board just past the quarter-hour mark.
Trent Alexander-Arnold scored by way of a great free kick.
Declan Rice chipped in with a goal to make sure of the win.
Arttu Hoskonen got a late consolation goal for Finland.
Pre-Game Insights: Manager Lee Carsley opted for a more coherent formation, helped in part by the return of striker Harry Kane.
Noni Madueke came on for Cole Palmer midway through the second half.
Levi Colwill was an unused substitute.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley appeared to withdraw himself from consideration for the job full-time after the Greece defeat, but he now has three wins from his four games in charge.
Lee Carsley has shown a willingness to try some new things and has a personal connection with all the young players from his time as under-21 coach.
